The paper deals with link classification in signed networks, which is a topic related to social networks and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents learning bounds and algorithms, which are related to machine learning and data mining, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses transductive learning settings, which are related to statistical learning theory, making cs.SD (Statistical Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper also deals with graph theory and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper is motivated by social balance theory, which is related to sociology and psychology, making cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) a possible sub-category.
